sent through my body

01:04:30.493 --> 01:04:32.411
were like dolphins swimming
through my bloodstream.

01:04:32.495 --> 01:04:35.289
The way she has opened me up,
she has penetrated deep inside of me

01:04:35.373 --> 01:04:38.000
and I know that I have penetrated deep,
deep inside of your daughter.

01:04:39.418 --> 01:04:40.670
Not... Not like that.

01:04:40.753 --> 01:04:42.380
I would love to

01:04:42.463 --> 01:04:45.508
when is necessary for...

01:04:45.633 --> 01:04:48.302
I want kids someday.
Not right now, of course,

01:04:48.386 --> 01:04:49.720
but when you're ready and when I'm ready,

01:04:49.804 --> 01:04:51.264
because I think this should
be a shared decision.

01:04:51.347 --> 01:04:53.307
This is a decision
that we should make together.

01:04:53.391 --> 01:04:55.643
But when you are ready, I will be ready.

01:04:56.811 --> 01:05:00.022
I am ready for you, if you will have me.

01:05:01.857 --> 01:05:03.192
Claire...

01:05:05.069 --> 01:05:06.654
What's your last name?

01:05:06.862 --> 01:05:08.114
M... McCune.

01:05:08.197 --> 01:05:09.740
Claire McCune,

01:05:11.117 --> 01:05:12.827
will you be my wife?

01:05:23.963 --> 01:05:26.841
Okay, funny man,
I'm sure your dad's waiting up.

01:05:28.175 --> 01:05:30.094
Don't worry, you'll see her tomorrow.

01:05:31.012 --> 01:05:32.179
Good night.

01:06:15.348 --> 01:06:16.390
It's just a penis.

01:06:17.391 --> 01:06:19.143
Every man has one.

01:06:19.435 --> 01:06:21.729
We're all animals of the Earth.

01:06:22.438 --> 01:06:24.482
Clothes when we eat.

01:07:59.118 --> 01:08:01.954
- You look happy.
- I am happy.

01:08:02.037 --> 01:08:03.205
Are you happy?

01:08:03.289 --> 01:08:05.249
Yeah. I'm here with you.

01:08:21.432 --> 01:08:25.310
O God, to whom mercy
and forgiveness belong,

01:08:25.770 --> 01:08:29.732
hear our prayer on behalf
of your servant Leslie Cash,

01:08:30.149 --> 01:08:33.109
whom you have taken out of the world.

01:08:33.319 --> 01:08:37.281
And because she put her
trust and hope in you,

01:08:37.782 --> 01:08:40.826
command that she be carried
safely home to Heaven

01:08:41.868 --> 01:08:46.122
and come to enjoy your eternal reward.

01:08:46.207 --> 01:08:47.374
- Amen.
- Amen.

01:08:50.127 --> 01:08:51.629
Come on, guys.

01:09:05.475 --> 01:09:07.144
Do you mind scooting over, sir?

01:09:17.488 --> 01:09:20.323
I did not know Leslie personally

01:09:21.325 --> 01:09:23.452
and I am poorer for it.

01:09:24.286 --> 01:09:28.791
I understand that she was a loving
mother who gave up her law practice

01:09:28.874 --> 01:09:30.209
to raise her children.

01:09:30.835 --> 01:09:32.502
Leslie loved her mother, Abigail,

01:09:32.586 --> 01:09:36.173
and her father, Jack, and their dogs,

01:09:36.966 --> 01:09:39.134
Harvey and Little Bear.

01:09:39.510 --> 01:09:42.429
They told me that she also loved gardening

01:09:42.805 --> 01:09:47.142
and classical music,
particularly Glenn Gould's versions

01:09:47.225 --> 01:09:49.520
of the Goldberg Variations.

01:09:50.437 --> 01:09:54.942
She also liked walks
in the moonlight on the beach.

01:09:55.818 --> 01:09:59.655
And she loved her husband,
Ben, and their children...

01:09:59.738 --> 01:10:02.950
I'll, uh, take that as my cue, if I may.

01:10:13.919 --> 01:10:17.298
First of all, Leslie practiced Buddhism,

01:10:17.965 --> 01:10:21.343
which, to her, was a philosophy
and not an organized religion.

01:10:21.427 --> 01:10:24.763
In fact, Leslie abhorred
all organized religions.

01:10:24.847 --> 01:10:28.267
To her, they were the most
dangerous fairy tales ever invented.

01:10:28.559 --> 01:10:33.022
Designed to elicit blind obedience and
strike fear into the hearts of the innocent

01:10:33.105 --> 01:10:34.648
and the uninformed.

01:10:34.732 --> 01:10:37.067
To her, the only thing worse than death

01:10:37.276 --> 01:10:39.403
would have been the knowledge
that her rotting flesh

01:10:39.486 --> 01:10:41.906
was to be trapped
for all eternity inside a big box

01:10:43.532 --> 01:10:45.701
and buried in the middle
of a fucking golf course.

01:10:49.163 --> 01:10:54.001
Although the absurdity of being eulogized
by someone that didn't even know her

01:10:54.084 --> 01:10:58.213
has exactly the kind of comedic flourish
that Leslie would have cherished.

01:10:58.547 --> 01:11:00.674
If nothing else, she had a sense of humor.

01:11:01.634 --> 01:11:05.179
I want to read something to all of you,
so you'll know what I mean.

01:11:06.138 --> 01:11:08.599
Leslie's last will and testament.

01:11:08.724 --> 01:11:11.268
And I quote, "In the event of my death,

01:11:11.352 --> 01:11:13.562
"I, Leslie Abigail Cash,

01:11:13.646 --> 01:11:15.689
"as a Buddhist, wish to be cremated.

01:11:15.773 --> 01:11:17.608
"My funeral, such as it is,

01:11:17.691 --> 01:11:20.194
"shall be a celebration of the life cycle,

01:11:20.277 --> 01:11:22.404
"with music and dancing.

01:11:22.863 --> 01:11:25.616
"After, it is my expressed
desire that my ashes

01:11:25.908 --> 01:11:28.243
"shall be taken to a nondescript location,

01:11:28.327 --> 01:11:30.704
"preferably public and heavily populated.

01:11:30.788 --> 01:11:34.375
"At which point my ashes,
promptly and unceremoniously,

01:11:34.458 --> 01:11:36.502
"are to be flushed
down the nearest toilet."

01:11:37.002 --> 01:11:38.796
End quote.

01:11:39.964 --> 01:11:41.173
Now, that's comedy.

01:11:41.256 --> 01:11:42.800
- All right, that's enough.
- I'm not finished.

01:11:42.883 --> 01:11:44.760
Hey, I'm not finished.

01:11:45.010 --> 01:11:46.387
- Dad!
- You're not listening to me!

01:11:46.512 --> 01:11:47.972
- This is not what she wanted!
- Dad!

01:11:48.055 --> 01:11:49.390
- Just keep moving forward.
- Let go of me!

01:11:49.473 --> 01:11:50.641
Okay, that's it, come on.

01:11:50.724 --> 01:11:52.851
- Dad!
- She's my wife!

01:11:52.935 --> 01:11:56.021
This is her will!
This is against her wishes!

01:11:56.730 --> 01:11:59.692
God damn it! We have songs to sing!

01:11:59.775 --> 01:12:00.943
Dad!

01:12:01.110 --> 01:12:02.987
If you'll open your books,

01:12:03.070 --> 01:12:09.118
we'll read this morning
from Matthew 18, verses 15-20.

01:12:45.070 --> 01:12:48.115
You are the worst thing that
has ever happened to my family.

01:12:48.240 --> 01:12:50.576
Why won't you respect
your daughter's wishes?

01:12:50.659 --> 01:12:52.119
Or your grandchildren's?

01:12:52.578 --> 01:12:53.912
Hi, kids.

01:12:54.913 --> 01:12:56.623
Hello, Grandpa, I'm Nai.

01:12:56.749 --> 01:12:58.500
Nai. We've never met.

01:12:58.584 --> 01:12:59.752
Gee, Abby.

01:12:59.835 --> 01:13:02.254
I'm sorry. Sorry.

01:13:05.591 --> 01:13:06.925
Hi, honey.

01:13:07.885 --> 01:13:10.888
Grandma!

01:13:11.096 --> 01:13:12.639
Hello, Grandma.

01:13:12.848 --> 01:13:16.101
We're all together. Isn't this wonderful?

01:13:16.185 --> 01:13:18.645
Abby and I are going to take
the children to the ceremony

01:13:18.771 --> 01:13:20.814
and then you can follow us to the house.

01:13:21.273 --> 01:13:23.901
They're my kids, they're staying with me.

01:13:23.984 --> 01:13:26.653
Children, I'm sorry
that you have to witness this,

01:13:26.779 --> 01:13:29.114
but I don't think your father
is fit to attend the funeral.

01:13:29.198 --> 01:13:31.116
We're not going to let you
put her in the ground!

01:13:31.200 --> 01:13:33.118
Who do you think the police
are going to listen to? Me?

01:13:33.786 --> 01:13:36.121
Or some hippie in a clown outfit?

01:13:36.872 --> 01:13:37.956
Come on, Abby.

01:13:38.040 --> 01:13:39.124
Where are we going?

01:13:39.208 --> 01:13:40.501
We're going to see Leslie. We have to go.

01:13:40.626 --> 01:13:42.878
- I'm visiting with the children.
- We have to see them at the house.

01:13:42.961 --> 01:13:44.546
Would you just give me
a minute with the children?

01:13:44.630 --> 01:13:46.006
Honey, honey, Leslie is waiting.

01:13:46.131 --> 01:13:47.966
Leslie is waiting. Come on.

01:13:49.510 --> 01:13:51.720
- Bye, Grandma.
- Bye, Grandma and Grandpa.

01:13:57.726 --> 01:13:59.645
Back on Steve, let's go.

01:14:00.145 --> 01:14:01.855
- Dad?
- Let's go.

01:14:01.980 --> 01:14:03.148
Dad, where are we going?

01:14:03.232 --> 01:14:04.733
We're going to stop this fucking funeral!

01:14:04.817 --> 01:14:06.485
- Dad!
- No!

01:14:06.568 --> 01:14:07.569
Dad!

01:14:08.403 --> 01:14:09.571
Dad, we can't go.

01:14:09.655 --> 01:14:10.864
Please, just listen to us.

01:14:10.989 --> 01:14:13.158
- Why can't we go to Mom's funeral?
- Because of Dad.

01:14:13.242 --> 01:14:14.535
- Because of his speech?
- Yes!

01:14:14.660 --> 01:14:17.246
Everyone shut up and sit down!
Sit the fuck down!

01:14:17.329 --> 01:14:18.497
- Dad.
- Silence!

01:14:19.039 --> 01:14:20.415
Put your goddamn seat belts on!

01:14:20.499 --> 01:14:21.875
- No! Stop Steve!
- You heard Grandpa!

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:23.252
He'll have us arrested if we show up!

01:14:23.335 --> 01:14:25.129
They are not stopping us from saving Mom!

01:14:25.212 --> 01:14:26.421
Dad, abort the mission!

01:14:26.505 --> 01:14:28.507
Let's just go home! Abort the mission!

01:14:28.590 --> 01:14:29.967
We are rescuing Mom!

01:14:30.050 --> 01:14:31.343
Mom is dead, okay, Dad? She's dead!

01:14:31.426 --> 01:14:32.845
This is not what she would
have wanted you to do!

01:14:33.011 --> 01:14:35.222
- They have no right!
- I don't want to lose you!

01:14:36.932 --> 01:14:40.435
Please. We can't lose you, too.

01:15:09.047 --> 01:15:10.632
Motherfuck!

01:16:26.875 --> 01:16:28.961
I have memories of Mom

01:16:30.462 --> 01:16:31.463
laughing.

01:16:35.133 --> 01:16:37.511
I... I can't even remember when that was.

01:16:45.811 --> 01:16:48.480
Mom had psychotic episodes.

01:16:49.690 --> 01:16:51.483
She had hallucinations.

01:16:54.486 --> 01:16:56.488
Of smashing our heads in with rocks.

01:16:57.489 --> 01:16:59.157
I heard them talking about it.

01:17:04.871 --> 01:17:07.249
Mom was sicker than any of us knew.

01:17:08.250 --> 01:17:10.002
Dad made her crazy.

01:17:14.840 --> 01:17:16.842
Dad's dangerous.

01:17:22.681 --> 01:17:24.850
You think our lives are so great.

01:17:25.267 --> 01:17:27.519
You think Dad is so perfect.

01:18:06.224 --> 01:18:08.685
Yale, Stanford, Princeton, Harvard,

01:18:08.769 --> 01:18:11.730
Dartmouth, MIT, Brown.

01:18:21.281 --> 01:18:22.574
Well done.

01:18:23.617 --> 01:18:24.785
Thank you.

01:18:25.369 --> 01:18:26.620
It's very impressive.

01:18:32.250 --> 01:18:34.544
I guess. Yeah.

01:18:37.589 --> 01:18:40.258
All this time you've been deceiving me?

01:18:43.053 --> 01:18:45.013
- What? No.
- I took you to the library,

01:18:45.097 --> 01:18:48.100
and you snuck around behind
my back taking SAT tests

01:18:48.225 --> 01:18:51.144
- and contacting universities?
- Dad, it's not like that.

01:18:51.269 --> 01:18:52.646
We're not an accredited home school,

01:18:52.771 --> 01:18:54.731
I don't know how the fuck you did it.

01:18:55.440 --> 01:18:57.526
- I guess you somehow...
- You don't understand.

01:18:57.609 --> 01:19:00.112
...managed to create acceptable
transcripts, got your work approved.

01:19:00.237 --> 01:19:01.279
Listen.

01:19:01.405 --> 01:19:02.614
All without my knowledge and approval.

01:19:02.739 --> 01:19:03.740
Listen, Dad, please.

01:19:03.824 --> 01:19:05.200
I don't know what's more impressive.

01:19:05.283 --> 01:19:06.952
The fact that you got into
all these fine schools

01:19:07.077 --> 01:19:10.455
or that for months you've been
lying directly to my face.

01:19:10.580 --> 01:19:11.915
It was Mom.

01:19:17.629 --> 01:19:20.632
She helped me with everything.
We did it together.

01:19:23.135 --> 01:19:25.804
- I just want to go to college.
- You speak six languages!

01:19:25.929 --> 01:19:27.389
You have high math, theoretical physics!

01:19:27.472 --> 01:19:28.890
Dad! But this is what I'm talking about!

01:19:28.974 --> 01:19:30.225
What the hell are these
people going to teach you?

01:19:30.308 --> 01:19:32.018
I know nothing!

01:19:32.144 --> 01:19:35.772
I know nothing!
I am a freak because of you!

01:19:35.981 --> 01:19:38.483
You made us freaks!

01:19:38.608 --> 01:19:40.485
And Mom knew that! She understood!

01:19:41.653 --> 01:19:46.658
Unless it comes out of a fucking book,
I don't know anything about anything!

01:20:12.017 --> 01:20:13.018
Dad?

01:20:15.145 --> 01:20:16.396
You should put some clothes on, buddy.

01:20:29.201 --> 01:20:31.995
No, stay on Steve. I'll be right back.

01:20:37.834 --> 01:20:39.127
- Where is he?
- No.

01:20:39.211 --> 01:20:40.295
Abby, I need Rell.

01:20:40.378 --> 01:20:41.421
It won't work like this, you know Jack.

01:20:41.546 --> 01:20:42.547
He's my son.

01:20:46.218 --> 01:20:47.427
All right.

01:20:48.887 --> 01:20:51.389
It's all about timing. Just be easy.

01:20:54.059 --> 01:20:55.393
Follow through.

01:21:00.065 --> 01:21:02.526
- Okay, get your things.
- Just a minute, please.

01:21:02.609 --> 01:21:03.860
Come on, Rell.

01:21:04.277 --> 01:21:05.946
I said, just a minute.

01:21:06.738 --> 01:21:09.533
I've clearly upset you and I apologize.

01:21:09.616 --> 01:21:11.076
You killed Mom!

01:21:11.159 --> 01:21:12.244
Oh.

01:21:21.920 --> 01:21:22.921
I heard you.

01:21:24.923 --> 01:21:26.424
I heard you fighting about where we live.

01:21:26.550 --> 01:21:29.427
Mom wanted to leave. I heard.

01:21:30.595 --> 01:21:33.431
Your mother and I made
certain decisions, together,

01:21:33.515 --> 01:21:34.849
about what was best for all of you.

01:21:34.933 --> 01:21:37.936
I'm going to live here
with Nana and Grandpa.

01:21:38.353 --> 01:21:42.941
That's not possible.
Come on, get your stuff. Let's go.

01:21:45.777 --> 01:21:46.778
Let's go!

01:21:47.779 --> 01:21:51.199
I hate you! I fucking hate you!

01:21:51.283 --> 01:21:52.284
Rellian.

01:21:54.953 --> 01:21:56.204
Rellian.

01:22:02.377 --> 01:22:04.713
What the fuck? That almost hit me!

01:22:04.796 --> 01:22:06.715
If I wanted to hit you,
I would have hit you.

01:22:06.798 --> 01:22:08.049
You just shot an arrow at me!

01:22:08.133 --> 01:22:10.218
You told me they were in school.

01:22:13.054 --> 01:22:14.306
They are.

01:22:15.056 --> 01:22:16.391
Leslie and I are their teachers.

01:22:16.474 --> 01:22:17.976
Are... Were their teachers.

01:22:18.059 --> 01:22:20.061
So you're teaching them to steal?

01:22:20.145 --> 01:22:21.146
Of course not.

01:22:21.229 --> 01:22:22.981
"Mission: Free the Food"?

01:22:24.816 --> 01:22:26.568
That was part of their training.

01:22:26.651 --> 01:22:28.653
So you're training them to steal?

01:22:29.988 --> 01:22:32.115
Their mother had just died.

01:22:32.324 --> 01:22:35.827
They were in shock, they were devastated,
they needed a distraction.

01:22:35.910 --> 01:22:37.329
So we made it Noam Chomsky Day.

01:22:37.454 --> 01:22:38.913
"Noam Chomsky Day."

01:22:38.997 --> 01:22:40.415
I don't even know who that is.

01:22:40.498 --> 01:22:43.627
That's the day you gave
my grandchildren real weapons.

01:22:46.671 --> 01:22:48.673
How did Rellian break his hand?

01:22:51.343 --> 01:22:54.929
He slip... He fell. And it's not broken.

01:22:55.013 --> 01:22:57.098
He was climbing
on a rock face in the rain.

01:22:57.182 --> 01:22:58.767
It was an accident.

01:22:58.850 --> 01:23:00.518
And it wasn't raining
when we were climbing.

01:23:00.644 --> 01:23:02.604
He has bruises over his whole body.

01:23:02.687 --> 01:23:04.939
Yeah, and scratches. We all have them.

01:23:05.023 --> 01:23:06.107
It's child abuse.

01:23:06.191 --> 01:23:09.194
Even if they make it through whatever
it is you're doing to them,

01:23:09.277 --> 01:23:12.113
they're going to be totally unprepared
for the real world.

01:23:12.197 --> 01:23:14.491
And I happen to think
the opposite is true.

01:23:15.700 --> 01:23:20.705
Rellian is legally old enough to choose,
and I intend to honor his wishes.

01:23:25.710 --> 01:23:27.712
This is my lawyer's card.

01:23:29.130 --> 01:23:31.299
Abby and I have decided
that we're going to file

01:23:31.383 --> 01:23:33.301
for custody of the children.

01:23:33.385 --> 01:23:34.719
Now, I know you don't own a telephone,

01:23:34.844 --> 01:23:37.889
but I suggest you find one
immediately and call him.

01:23:38.390 --> 01:23:41.226
Because I would hate to have
to issue a warrant for your arrest.

01:23:41.309 --> 01:23:42.727
He's my son.

01:23:43.353 --> 01:23:45.355
I'm not leaving without him, Jack.

01:23:45.814 --> 01:23:47.023
Fine.

01:23:51.736 --> 01:23:55.365
Who's this? Hey, hello, Bill, how are you?

01:23:55.740 --> 01:23:59.327
It's Jack Bertrang from up in Coronado.

01:23:59.411 --> 01:24:03.164
Listen, I think I just saw a prowler
wandering around outside on my grounds.

01:24:03.248 --> 01:24:06.376
I wonder if you'd send a car.
Thanks. Yeah.

01:24:08.586 --> 01:24:13.091
I hope you can explain Rellian's
injuries to the police, because I can't.

01:24:33.528 --> 01:24:35.739
- Yes, thanks very much.
- Sure thing, Mr. Bertrang.

01:24:47.542 --> 01:24:50.879
Okay, prisoner located.

01:24:50.962 --> 01:24:54.048
Second floor, second window,
above the garage.

01:24:57.385 --> 01:24:58.511
Target locked.

01:24:59.471 --> 01:25:00.638
Bring him home, Vesp.

01:26:25.974 --> 01:26:27.058
Dad!

01:26:27.141 --> 01:26:28.977
- Vespyr!
- Dad!

01:26:29.936 --> 01:26:32.355
- Vespyr!
- Dad!

01:26:56.546 --> 01:26:58.214
Mr. Cash?

01:27:05.847 --> 01:27:08.516
She's got a decent concussion,
but we did a CAT scan,

01:27:08.600 --> 01:27:10.435
and there's absolutely
no damage to the brain.

01:27:10.852 --> 01:27:14.397
She does have a slight fracture across
the tibia and fibula of her left leg.

01:27:14.480 --> 01:27:18.276
She's going to need a neck brace
and a cast, but otherwise she's fine.

01:27:18.818 --> 01:27:20.236
Can I show you something?

01:27:20.945 --> 01:27:23.489
Uh, this is the top vertebrae here.

01:27:23.823 --> 01:27:27.160
This dark line, it's hard to see,
but that's the fracture line.

01:27:28.411 --> 01:27:30.121
What was she doing on a roof?

01:27:32.665 --> 01:27:34.751
Just playing.

01:27:35.710 --> 01:27:37.545
Well, for a girl her age,
she's unusually strong.

01:27:38.421 --> 01:27:39.464
Yeah.

01:27:39.547 --> 01:27:40.965
There's seven vertebrae in the neck.

01:27:41.049 --> 01:27:44.177
